  "prompt": "Should I write \"Dear Professors\" or \"Dear Prof. A, Prof. B and Prof. C\", while writing an email to 3 professors?",
  "response": "It depends on the context and your level of familiarity with the professors:\n\n1. If you know all three professors personally or have been in communication with them before, use their individual names (e.g., \"Dear Prof. A, Prof. B, and Prof. C\").\n\n2. If this is a more formal or first-time communication, or if you don't know them well, \"Dear Professors\" is appropriate and professional.\n\n3. If one professor is the primary contact or lead, you might address them specifically and CC the others.\n\nWhen in doubt, \"Dear Professors\" is a safe, respectful choice that covers all three recipients.",
